    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This E46 M3 is a driver-focused example featuring the S54B32 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, renowned for its independent throttle bodies and 8,000 RPM redline. Mechanically, the dual-VANOS system has been overhauled, and the rod bearings were addressed as preventative maintenance. Power is routed through a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission to a GKN variable M differential lock, ensuring exceptional power delivery out of corners. The chassis is structurally sound with documented rear subframe reinforcement and an upgraded cooling system featuring an aluminum radiator. Suspension geometry is maintained by Bilstein B16 coilovers and reinforced strut towers, providing sharp turn-in and minimal lateral roll. While the exterior shows honest signs of road use, the drivetrain and kinematic components are dialed in for peak performance.",
